# Enterprise Architecture Standards

- Design for modularity: split responsibilities into cohesive components with clear boundaries.
- Use stable interfaces and dependency injection where component swapping is expected.
- Prefer composition over inheritance-heavy coupling.
- Keep behavior configuration-driven; avoid hardcoded environment/business rules.
- Add extension points (factories/registries/hooks) only where they solve a current requirement.
- Keep modules loosely coupled and testable in isolation.
- Include error handling and observability in production paths (structured logs/metrics where relevant).
- For large changes, ship incrementally with reversible slices and explicit migration notes.
